Version: Python 3 
File extension: .py 

Problem: https://www.hackerrank.com/challenges/np-transpose-and-flatten/problem 

Solution:

import numpy
n, m = map(int, input().split())
array = numpy.array([input().strip().split() for _ in range(n)], int)
print (array.transpose())
print (array.flatten())

Sample input: 2 4
              1 2 3 4
              5 6 7 8
              
Sample output: [[1 5]
               [2 6]
               [3 7]
               [4 8]]
               [1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8]
